04/09/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Customs authorities seized 473kg of heroin at the border with Bulgaria on Thursday (September 3rd). 
A trained dog found the drugs hidden in eight copy machines aboard a truck bound for Germany. 
The drugs seized at the Kapikule border checkpoint are estimated to be worth about 6.6m euros. 
The driver of the vehicle was arrested. 
(Anadolu news agency, AFP - 04/09/09)
